When using the "search user" form in Crowd on an LDAP connector directory it adds the '*' character at the beginning and the ending of the search string and if that was not bad enough it searches like this with an OR clause over all attributes that are known to Crowd... even on an LDAP where all attributes are indexed this causes useless load and takes a long time to finish. here is an example of what filter is used when searching for the string "patrick.camenzind": 
{code}(|(uid=*patrick.camenzind*)(cn=*patrick.camenzind*)(givenName=*patrick.camenzind*)(sn=*patrick.camenzind*)(mail=*patrick.camenzind*)){code}
It should only be searched for the string that was actually entered to the form (without stars if not explicitly typed like that) and possibly there should be a dropdown box to select the attribute to search on.

